cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY. 

The paper focuses on using a pre-trained CNN model for visual loop closure detection in SLAM, which is a problem in robotics. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also extensively evaluates the performance of CNN-based image representations in comparison with state-of-the-art hand-crafted features, which falls under the scope of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of pre-trained CNN models also involves techniques from cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the speed of feature extraction, which is relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
